 align=left class=m><span class=title>   You know what we need, so tell them!!</span><hr size=1> I see this time and time again. Mages underpowered (true in some cases, not in others). What is the one little spell that would completely eradicate this in an instant? Everyone knows its but I NEVER hear anyone asking for it?<br>
<br>
<br>
SNARE!!!!!!<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;But thats a treehugger thing, its roots that come out of the ground and grab the critter, and Darkness is differnt, its all creepy and deathy.&quot; Well, whats difference? Effect? Duration? No. Coding? Guarantee not. Call it what you like but give us a movement rate spell. Hell, even a crappy root (that I can cast AS A LVL52 for less resists rather than one cast from a 41 NPC) would be better than nothing. EVERY other caster has something in their arsenal to slow/stop/confuse/stun an opponent, why not mages? The weaknesses of the mage are due to its complete lack of crowd control. Earth pet root? OK, a root cast by an NPC 8 to 12 lvls below you, great. Very unlikely to stick and broken early almost every time on a 35+ malised mob. <br>
<br>
I know this is a little long and I do not intend in any way to belittle other classes for having it. I love my mage, but see no unbalancing reason for mages not having it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Pneladobaryn</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(6/29/00 2:16:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Interesting Idea</span><hr size=1> It would be interesting to see that, especially if they kinda shaped it to the mage class.  For example, call it soemthing like &quot;Elemental Encasement&quot; that surrounds the targets feet with heavy matter, thus slowing him.<br>
<br>
If it were implemented in that sort of fashion, I think it would be extremely cool, but I would not wanna see the mage just get Snare  (like that exact spell being put in our arsenal w/o any adjustment).  I dont even care if what mages did get does the same exact thing, the name and description alone would make it cool from a roleplaying perspective.<br>
<br>
