 class besides mages have NO movement rate spell. Correct. There's not one. I believe magically controlling/limiting the movement of opponents is a general ability of a magic user. This is upheld by the fact that every casting class in the game (including hybrids who are melee based) can control the movement of enemies. Roleplaying is fine, but I personally would rather be able to keep that Mature Wurm from frying my bacon rather than trying to talk him out of it. Jboots? Sure. They're a Good Thing, but if youve spent much time in Kunark youll find that you won't outrun much with them. Only thing I've seen that will outrun even a lvl 35 Kunark Rhino is wolfform. Sowed? When it hits you turn around and run and watch as it scrolls 70pt hits till youre dead. It's odd. In early beta, Mages were GROSSLY overpowered. A mage and his pet were FAR better than a Wizard and a Warrior grouped, no kidding. This was clearly wrong, so Mages were nerfed hard and rightly so. But since then not much thought has been put into them as a class, so they remain where they were. Mages were intended to be self-reliant so please make them more so. It would be very simple. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showPrevMessage?topicID=27.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showNextMessage?topicID=27.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.threadControl?topicID=27.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border